connect4.name: connect4
connect4.description:
Connect4 game for 1-1 chat rooms in Chaatz.
Users can start a game from Android/iOS clients from within
a chatroom, make a move and transmit it to their chat partner
via XMPP.

This game relies on the native chaatz client for communication
and persistence of data.

TODO LIST:
- Integrate game with native client (iOS)
- Version for facebook
- Check types for strings
- Clean up functions.js
- Need to check in loadGame and packageGame that the string is correct before passing

"Would be nice" list:
- Animate entrance and exit (Probably needs to be done on native)
- Swipe down to close the game

FLOW:
- Check whose turn it is and set boolean.
- Load previous game state
- Render
- Make a move
- Check winner
- If win, show WIN UI
- Package outgoing
- Close game

classitems.description:
Called when the user taps a column.
- Appends a token HTML block to the DOM at the column div location. 
- Runs a jQuery animation of the token falling to the bottom.
- After the animation, the 2D array that represents the game is updated.
- A check is performed to see if anybody has won.
- my_turn boolean is set to false, preventing another turn.
- UI is updated.
classitems.name: makeMove

classitems.description:
Changes the game's 2D array to match the move made.
Only traverses the column that was tapped.
classitems.name: updateGameArray

classitems.description: Calculates the column height (number of tokens within a column).
classitems.name: getColumnHeight

return.description: columnHeight - The height of the column in tokens.

classitems.description:
Renders the game UI based on the 2D game array.
The UI includes:
- Tokens
- My turn box
- Player info
classitems.name: render

classitems.description:
Add jQuery click listeners to the columns.
Note: in the css I have added pointer-events:none
so click events go through overlaid UI elements
classitems.name: bindEvents

classitems.description:
Checks the game's 2D array to see if anybody has won.
If a winner is found, a game over is triggered.
classitems.name: gameOver

return.description: gameOverStatus - True if a game is over.

classitems.description:
Changes the game to the game over state by:
- Updating UI
- Popping up a message
classitems.name: printGameReadable

classitems.description: Replays the last move in the UI for the benefit of the receiving player.
classitems.name: showLastMove

classitems.description:
Packages all data necessary for outgoing communication
in JSON format.
classitems.name: outputGameInJSONFormat

classitems.description: Called when a move is recieved?
classitems.name: receiveMove

classitems.description:
Returns the string representation of the game's 2D array.
Removes commas.
classitems.name: packageGameToString

classitems.description:
Takes the string representation of the game and
returns a 2D array representing the game.
Basic checking (if the input string is less than 42 chars
it will default).
classitems.name: loadGameFromString

classitems.description:
Prints out the current game state in a readable way.
Currently a stub only
classitems.name: printGameReadable

classitems.description: Enumerates the tokens so they can be read more easily in the code.
classitems.name: tokens
